{{runtime}} / {{framework}}

## Patterns

### Component Structure
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Props interface at top of file
- Default exports for pages, named for components
- Colocate tests: `Component.test.tsx` next to component

### State Management
- Local state: `useState` / `useReducer`
- Global state: {{state_library}}
- Server state: {{server_state_library}}

### Routing
- File-based routing in `src/app/` (App Router)
- Client components marked with `'use client'`
- Layouts for shared UI, pages for routes

### API Calls
- Use `fetch` or {{api_client}} for server components
- Client-side: SWR / React Query
- Error boundaries for graceful failures

## Constraints

### DO NOT
- Import server-only code in client components
- Use `any` type - use `unknown` or proper types
- Put business logic in components - extract to hooks/utils
- Mutate props - treat as read-only

## Watch

### Auto-alerts
- New component without tests → suggest adding
- Component >300 lines → suggest splitting
- Missing TypeScript types → warn
- Direct DOM access in React → block

